A total of 48 babies were born in the North West province on New Year s Day, the provincial health department said on Monday. Spokesperson Tebogo Lekgethwane said 30 girls and 18 boys were born in the province. This figure represents reports from facilities that have responded. There are facilities that might have not reported, particularly in deep rural areas, he said. Sixteen babies 10 girls and six boys were born in the Bojanala district, while eight babies five girls and three boys were born in the Dr Ruth Segomotsi Mompati district. In the Ngaka Modiri Molema district 11 babies seven girls and four boys were born, and in the Dr Kenneth Kaunda district 13 babies were born eight girls and five boys. African News Agency (ANA)